1. INTRODUCTION ‚Äî THE LIMITS OF VECTOR MEMORY

Traditional AI memory systems rely on:

1. Vector embeddings

Represent text as high-dimensional floating-point vectors.

2. Similarity search (kNN / FAISS / HNSW / ANN search)

Find closest vectors.

3. Context injection

Retrieved text is stuffed back into the LLM‚Äôs prompt.

This works for:
	‚Ä¢	factual recall
	‚Ä¢	document search
	‚Ä¢	basic conversation history

But fails at:
	‚Ä¢	narrative continuity
	‚Ä¢	symbolic coherence
	‚Ä¢	conceptual identity
	‚Ä¢	drift resistance
